Input.question2: When did China first have a year at the Winter Olympics but not at the Summer Olympics?
Input.question3: What was the last year that China appeared at both the Summer and Winter Olympics in the same year?
Answer.Res1: The Olympics include sports competitions between international athletes, and they are held every four years both in the winter and the summer months. Therefore, China's latest appearance  in the Olympics was in the 2022 winter season.
Answer.Res2: A country, or team, may participate in both, or neither, of that year's winter or summer olympics(international sports games where teams compete).  Therefore, China first had a year at the Winter Olympics but not the Summer Olympics in 1980.
Answer.Res3: In the Summer and Winter Olympics, where teams/countries have athletes compete against other athletes in international games every 4 years, a  country can choose whether or not to participate in both, one, or none of the games for that year/season.  Therefore, 1988 was the last year that China appeared at both the Summer and Winter Olympics in the same year.

Input.name: Republic of Algeria
Input.question1: How long after the French occupation of Algeria was its independence?
Input.question2: How many years longer was the time between  Hammadid dynasty and the Zayyanid dynasty and the Rustamid dynasty and the Zirid dynasty?
Input.question3: Prior to Al Jazâ'ir, which dynasty lasted the longest?
Answer.Res1: French occupation of Algeria was on 5 July 1830. Its independence was on 5 July 1962. Therefore, its independence was 132 years after the French occupation of Algeria.
Answer.Res2: Hammadid dynasty was in 1015 and the Zayyanid dynasty was in 1236. It means the time between Hammadid dynasty and the Zayyanid dynasty was 221 years. Rustamid dynasty was in 776 and the Zirid dynasty was in 972. It means the time between Rustamid dynasty and the Zirid dynasty was 196 years. Therefore, the time between Hammadid dynasty and the Zayyanid dynasty was 25 years longer than the time between Rustamid dynasty and the Zirid dynasty.
Answer.Res3: Zayyanid dynasty lasted for 280 years which is more than any dynasty except Al Jazâ'ir. Therefore, ​prior to Al Jazâ'ir, Zayyanid dynasty lasted the longest.

Answer.Res1: A football team's first international game is played against another country(vs a local/regional team), and its UEFA U-21 Championship happens when it beats out all the other countries except one. Denmark Under-21's First international happened in 1976, and its UEFA U-21 Championship appearance happened in 1978.  Therefore, Denmark's UEFA U-21's Championship appearance happened 2 years after its Under-21's First international.
Answer.Res2: The first international matchup for a football team includes the first game a team plays against another country, as opposed to local or regional matches.  Therfore, the Danish Football Association had its first international matchup in 1976.
Answer.Res3: The Olympics are held every 4 years, and a football team's first Olympic appearance happens in the year that they outscore all of their opponents except one. Therefore, the Danish Football Association U-21 made its first Olympic appearance in 1992.
